<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-934] Stacked cases with switch</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-934</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I stack several case branches to be handled by the same statements I get an parser error: Unkown type: &quot;case&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;switch(1) {&lt;br/&gt;
  case 1:&lt;br/&gt;
  case 2:&lt;br/&gt;
    println &quot;1 or 2&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    break&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
